INTRODUCTION AND READING OF BILLS

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Sanitation and Solid Waste Management
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to regulating publicly accessible collection bins.
EventItemMatterName: Regulating publicly accessible collection bins.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Higher Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign, A.8859/S.4469A, to amend the Education Law, in relation to hazing, serving alcohol to minors and illegal drug offenses.
EventItemMatterName: Amend the Education Law, in relation to hazing, serving alcohol to minors and illegal drug offenses. (A.8859/S.4469A)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Criminal Justice Services
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Senate to pass S.5740 and the Governor to sign such legislation into law, which would amend the New York State Correction Law by enhancing training for staff in residential mental health treatment unit programs inside correctional facilities.
EventItemMatterName: Enhancing training for staff in residential mental health treatment unit programs inside correctional facilities. (S.5740)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York City Department of Education to enforce Chancellor’s Regulation A-801, which requires that students on school buses wear seat belts until the bus comes to a destination stop.
EventItemMatterName: Requires that students on school buses wear seat belts until the bus comes to a destination stop.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Department of Education to calculate salaries of teachers in the New York City public school system based on the Department’s central budget rather than an individual school’s budget.
EventItemMatterName: DOE to calculate salaries of teachers in the NYC public school system based on the Department’s central budget rather than an individual school’s budget.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to arterial roadway towing.
EventItemMatterName: Arterial roadway towing.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York in relation to requirements and enforcement of newsrack provisions.
EventItemMatterName: Requirements and enforcement of newsrack provisions.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution approving the new designation and changes in the designation of certain organizations to receive funding in the Expense Budget.
EventItemMatterName: Approving the new designation and changes in the designation of certain organizations to receive funding in the Expense Budget.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York in relation to modular newsracks.
EventItemMatterName: Modular newsracks.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Consumer Affairs
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring restaurants to disclose when gratuity is included in the total cost of services.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring restaurants to disclose when gratuity is included in the total cost of services.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to information required to be posted by owners of residential dwellings during utility outages and other emergencies.
EventItemMatterName: Information required to be posted by owners of residential dwellings during utility outages and other emergencies.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to requiring that no videotape, or its contents, produced by an agency be destroyed or otherwise disposed of and that the head of each agency transmit to the municipal reference and research center such material in a timely manner.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring that no videotape, or its contents, produced by an agency be destroyed or otherwise disposed of and that the head of each agency transmit to the municipal reference and research center such material in a timely manner.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to notification of community boards of changes of regulations relating to traffic.
EventItemMatterName: Notification of community boards of changes of regulations relating to traffic.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Technology
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to providing public notice of production permits.
EventItemMatterName: Providing public notice of production permits.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Women's Issues
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Senate to pass and President to sign companion legislation to H.R. 863, which would establish a commission to study the creation of a National Women’s History Museum.
EventItemMatterName: Creation of a National Women’s History Museum. (H.R. 863)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution supporting a statewide and national ban on nontherapeutic uses of antibiotics in livestock production and calling upon the United States Congress to pass and the President to sign the Preventing Antibiotic Resistance Act (S. 1256) and the Preservation of Antibiotics for Medical Treatment Act (H.R. 1150).
EventItemMatterName: Preventing Antibiotic Resistance Act (S. 1256) and the Preservation of Antibiotics for Medical Treatment Act (H.R. 1150).

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to written responses by the board of standards and appeals
EventItemMatterName: Written explanations by the board of standards and appeals.

EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to a comprehensive cultural plan.
EventItemMatterName: Comprehensive cultural plan.

EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to mitigation of construction noise within seventy-five feet of a school.
EventItemMatterName: Mitigation of construction noise within seventy-five feet of a school.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York City Department of Education to bring more mentoring programs into schools to combat bullying and violence, as called for in the Stop School Violence online petition campaign by Anthony Vargas, a local high school student.
